         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">4/8/77. ¶  ¶ I was touched and delighted, dear Mr Shillinglaw, when yesterday I heard of our friend Giles, ¶ Possibly Ernest Giles, who arrived in Melbourne from Adelaide 2 July 1877 (Australasian(Mel...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">77.08.04</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Shillinglaw</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Box 244/3 Shillinglaw papers, La Trobe Australian manuscripts collection, State Library of Victoria, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">4/8/77.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was touched and delighted, dear Mr Shillinglaw, when yesterday I heard of our friend Giles,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Possibly Ernest Giles, who arrived in Melbourne from Adelaide 2 July 1877 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Australasian</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Melbourne), 7 July<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1877, p. 14.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that you stood up for me in such a manly manner against one of my most powerful adversaries. I have done the man never any harm; contrarily when he went to Philadelphia I wrote<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">kind words</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>about him to the great Asa Gray!<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to A. Gray, 25 December 1875. The man referred to was G. C. Levey, who was Secretary to the Victorian Exhibition Commissioners at the Philadelphia Centennial Exhibition in 1876.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>He knows nothing about me and my Department, absolutely nothing, at least no more than any layman. I feel your generous feeling for rectitude all the more, as I have no claims on your consideration.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully &amp; gratefully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
      </body>
